<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Form Processing Demo</title>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>User Input Form</h1>

  <form action="/process_form" method="post">
    <label for="name">Name:</label>
    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required><br><br>

    <label for="email">Email:</label>
    <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required><br><br>

    <textarea id="message" name="message" placeholder="Your message"></textarea><br><br>

    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
  </form>

  <p>Your data will be processed on the server and stored securely in a database.</p>

</body>
</html>
```

**Behind the Scenes (Server-Side Script - Example using PHP):**

```php
<?php
  // 1. Get form data
  $name = $_POST['name'];
  $email = $_POST['email'];
  $message = $_POST['message'];

  // 2. Validate data (example: check email format)
  if (!filter_var($email, FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL)) {
    echo "Invalid email address";
    exit;
  }

  // 3. Sanitize data (prevent XSS attacks)
  $name = htmlspecialchars($name);
  $message = htmlspecialchars($message);

  // 4. Connect to database (example using MySQL)
  $conn = new mysqli("localhost", "username", "password", "database_name");

  // 5. Prepare and execute SQL query to store data
  $sql = "INSERT INTO users (name, email, message) VALUES ('$name', '$email', '$message')";

  if ($conn->query($sql) === TRUE) {
    echo "Data stored successfully!";
  } else {
    echo "Error: " . $sql . "<br>" . $conn->error;
  }

  // 6. Close database connection
  $conn->close();
?>
```

**Explanation:**

* **Client-Side (HTML):** The form collects user input and sends it to the server using the `POST` method.
* **Server-Side (PHP):**
    * The server receives the form data.
    * It validates and sanitizes the data to ensure its integrity and security.
    * It connects to a database (e.g., MySQL) to store the data.
    * It executes a SQL query to insert the data into a table.
    * It sends a response back to the client, confirming successful storage or indicating any errors.

